(gasps)

107
00:04:48,143 --> 00:04:49,583
(grunts)

108
00:04:49,579 --> 00:04:52,689
Oh, thank heavens.
An adult has arrived to help me.

109
00:04:52,685 --> 00:04:54,955
No, no, no.
I'm just here to observe.

110
00:04:54,956 --> 00:04:56,186
(grunts)

111
00:04:56,192 --> 00:04:58,402
Uh, how would you like
to play hockey?

112
00:04:58,396 --> 00:05:00,496
Haw-haw... key?

113
00:05:00,501 --> 00:05:02,341
It's the most messed-up sport
in the world.

114
00:05:02,337 --> 00:05:04,737
It's like a prison riot
but with less rules.

115
00:05:04,743 --> 00:05:08,123
And you, you would play
the best position of all...

116
00:05:08,116 --> 00:05:09,646
the goon.

117
00:05:09,653 --> 00:05:11,023
Goon...

118
00:05:11,022 --> 00:05:12,222
Pretty word.

119
00:05:12,224 --> 00:05:13,834
What it mean?

120
00:05:13,828 --> 00:05:17,898
It's that sweet spot between
a thug and an enforcer.

121
00:05:17,902 --> 00:05:20,612
Anyone who comes near
the best players on the team,

122
00:05:20,608 --> 00:05:22,608
the goon turns their face
into mustard.

123
00:05:22,612 --> 00:05:25,552
(chuckles) You're exactly
what my team needs.

124
00:05:25,551 --> 00:05:27,721
Team? I don't do teams.

125
00:05:27,722 --> 00:05:29,062
Sorry.

126
00:05:29,058 --> 00:05:30,628
Not my pierogies!

127
00:05:30,628 --> 00:05:33,498
My Oma makes them
but once a week.

128
00:05:33,499 --> 00:05:36,109
(groans)
I got to deal with this.

129
00:05:36,105 --> 00:05:37,535
Nah, I get it.

130
00:05:37,542 --> 00:05:39,712
People look at scuzzes like us
like we got the plague.

131
00:05:39,713 --> 00:05:42,923
Which, when I did,
it weren't even bubonic.

132
00:05:42,919 --> 00:05:46,129
Our schedule, in case
you change your mind, there.

133
00:05:46,125 --> 00:05:47,455
Maybe we'll both find out

134
00:05:47,461 --> 00:05:49,231
what it feels
like to be winners.

135
00:05:49,231 --> 00:05:51,371
- (grunting)
- Hmm. Hmm. Hmm. Hmm.

136
00:05:56,178 --> 00:05:58,048
Full steam ahead, lads.

137
00:05:58,049 --> 00:05:59,349
We make for the goal,

138
00:05:59,351 --> 00:06:01,991
and damn their
neutral zone trap.

139
00:06:01,990 --> 00:06:03,590
(laughing)

140
00:06:03,594 --> 00:06:06,574
Oh, another weekend
murdered by kids' sports.

141
00:06:06,567 --> 00:06:08,337
How come this is
the only league in the world

142
00:06:08,336 --> 00:06:10,266
without a labor dispute?

143
00:06:10,273 --> 00:06:11,943
Unionize, cowards!

144
00:06:11,944 --> 00:06:13,484
SEA CAPTAIN: Yarr!

145
00:06:13,479 --> 00:06:16,419
(grunts)
I'm getting killed out there!

146
00:06:16,419 --> 00:06:18,419
So you get a little dinged up.

147
00:06:18,423 --> 00:06:20,903
You ever seen the children's
wing at the hospital?

148
00:06:20,895 --> 00:06:23,395
They got murals on the walls.
You'll love it.

149
00:06:23,399 --> 00:06:26,539
Everywhere you look...
rainbow, rainbow, rainbow.

150
00:06:26,540 --> 00:06:28,310
The whole league
knows all they have to do

151
00:06:28,309 --> 00:06:29,879
is beat me up and they win.

152
00:06:29,879 --> 00:06:31,879
Yeah, you're right,
it's hopeless.

153
00:06:31,883 --> 00:06:34,423
There ain't nobody
who's gonna walk into this rink

154
00:06:34,421 --> 00:06:36,161
and turn me into a winner.

155
00:06:36,158 --> 00:06:38,058
No how, no when.

156
00:06:38,062 --> 00:06:41,172
Did somebody order a psycho?

157
00:06:41,168 --> 00:06:42,138
Oh.

158
00:06:42,137 --> 00:06:43,407
Where do you want me, Crotch?

159
00:06:43,406 --> 00:06:45,576
Uh, it-it's "coach."
But just get out there.

160
00:06:45,578 --> 00:06:47,578
Get out there and do your thing.

161
00:06:48,349 --> 00:06:49,849
(grunts)

162
00:06:49,853 --> 00:06:52,793
♪

163
00:07:00,006 --> 00:07:02,076
(buzzing)

164
00:07:02,077 --> 00:07:03,307
- We won!
- We did it!

165
00:07:03,313 --> 00:07:04,523
- Oh, my gosh!
- (cheering)

166
00:07:04,516 --> 00:07:06,746
- My life has meaning!
- (blowing whistle)

167
00:07:06,753 --> 00:07:09,163
As I've been screaming
for the last 15 minutes,

168
00:07:09,158 --> 00:07:12,498
- all players must be
wearing skates.
- Oh, come on.

169
00:07:12,497 --> 00:07:13,967
There's no way that that...

170
00:07:13,968 --> 00:07:15,368
Oh, there it is.

171
00:07:15,370 --> 00:07:17,540
Rule number one:
"No cafeteria trays."

172
00:07:17,542 --> 00:07:19,912
The Bar Flyers forfeit.
The game is over.

173
00:07:19,913 --> 00:07:22,153
ALL:
Aw!

174
00:07:22,150 --> 00:07:23,390
You said I'd get to win.

175
00:07:23,386 --> 00:07:26,556
All I did was make
everyone else a loser, too.

176
00:07:26,560 --> 00:07:30,530
Loser? No, no,
you-you were amazing out there.

177
00:07:30,534 --> 00:07:33,744
- I was?
- Kid, you are
a natural born goon.

178
00:07:33,741 --> 00:07:37,281
A real diamond in the urinal.
All you need is some training.

179
00:07:37,280 --> 00:07:40,790
And I'm gonna make sure
that you learn from the best.

180
00:07:42,090 --> 00:07:44,600
Welcome to Top Goon.

181
00:07:44,596 --> 00:07:45,866
It's beautiful.

182
00:07:45,865 --> 00:07:48,365
I'm gonna learn so hard, Moe.

183
00:07:48,369 --> 00:07:52,209
- I won't let you down.
- I know you won't, kid.

184
00:07:53,847 --> 00:07:56,617
- What was that?
- Oh, I just tousled your hair.

185
00:07:56,620 --> 00:07:59,090
Ain't nobody
ever done that before?

186
00:07:59,091 --> 00:08:00,331
Uh...

187
00:08:00,327 --> 00:08:01,827
Keep going.

188
00:08:01,830 --> 00:08:04,540
Yeah, my arm's getting
a little tired, here.

189
00:08:04,536 --> 00:08:07,066
- That's your problem.
- (sighing): All right.

190
00:08:11,516 --> 00:08:13,516
Welcome to Top Goon.

191
00:08:13,520 --> 00:08:14,990
I'd like to introduce you
to your faculty,

192
00:08:14,989 --> 00:08:17,559
the most feared men
to ever lace 'em up.

193
00:08:17,562 --> 00:08:19,372
Dave "The Hammer" Schultz.

194
00:08:19,365 --> 00:08:20,665
That's just a nickname.

195
00:08:20,668 --> 00:08:23,708
My given name is
David "The Hammer" Schultz.

196
00:08:23,707 --> 00:08:25,747
Stu "The Grim Reaper" Grimson.

197
00:08:25,745 --> 00:08:28,215
