♪ At the good ol' hockey game ♪

227
00:09:35,584 --> 00:09:37,794
♪ Oh, the good ol' hockey game ♪

228
00:09:37,789 --> 00:09:39,959
♪ Is the best game
you can name ♪

229
00:09:39,959 --> 00:09:43,029
♪ And the best game
you can name ♪

230
00:09:43,032 --> 00:09:44,602
♪ Is the good ol'
hockey game. ♪

231
00:09:44,602 --> 00:09:46,842
(groans)

232
00:09:46,840 --> 00:09:47,840
Mm...

233
00:09:49,044 --> 00:09:51,124
Aw...

234
00:09:51,115 --> 00:09:53,045
Huh?

235
00:09:53,052 --> 00:09:54,422
Hey, sorry I'm late.

236
00:09:54,421 --> 00:09:56,091
I couldn't unlock the Maps app.

237
00:09:56,091 --> 00:09:59,531
(chuckling): My phone don't
recognize my face as a face.

238
00:09:59,532 --> 00:10:01,602
I can't believe you came!

239
00:10:01,603 --> 00:10:03,943
I wouldn't miss this
for my own mother's funeral.

240
00:10:03,941 --> 00:10:06,411
I made that choice
and I'm good with it.

241
00:10:06,412 --> 00:10:08,482
Hey, Moe.
How's it going?

242
00:10:08,483 --> 00:10:10,153
You know these guys?

243
00:10:10,153 --> 00:10:12,963
I used to be the bartender
in the penalty box

244
00:10:12,959 --> 00:10:14,759
at the Philadelphia Spectrum.

245
00:10:14,762 --> 00:10:17,032
(chuckles)
My tip jar was full of teeth.

246
00:10:17,033 --> 00:10:20,213
I got Phil Esposito's
whole mouth somewheres.

247
00:10:20,206 --> 00:10:21,406
♪

248
00:10:21,408 --> 00:10:23,978
Muntz, recite the goon code.

249
00:10:23,981 --> 00:10:26,491
I am a goon.
I protect my primary.

250
00:10:26,485 --> 00:10:28,515
And... that's pretty much it.

251
00:10:28,524 --> 00:10:32,534
Nelson Muntz, you've out-thugged
every gorilla in your class.

252
00:10:32,532 --> 00:10:35,242
You are... Top Goon!

253
00:10:35,236 --> 00:10:37,236
♪

254
00:10:40,480 --> 00:10:42,790
I did... not bad?

255
00:10:42,785 --> 00:10:44,285
Hey, you did more than that.

256
00:10:44,288 --> 00:10:45,518
You did not horrible.

257
00:10:45,524 --> 00:10:49,774
Now come on, I got a graduation
present lined up for youse.

258
00:10:50,668 --> 00:10:53,108
From up here,
the wads look like ants.

259
00:10:53,105 --> 00:10:55,575
Hey, you-you want to drop
pickled eggs on them?

260
00:10:55,578 --> 00:10:57,108
Sure!

261
00:10:58,049 --> 00:10:59,949
Yeah, Duff lets me
use their blimp

262
00:10:59,953 --> 00:11:03,063
'cause I buy up all the beer
that the employees drown in.

263
00:11:03,059 --> 00:11:05,999
Pretty sweet
for a couple of scuzzes.

264
00:11:05,998 --> 00:11:08,738
Yeah, it's a big world
down there, kid.

265
00:11:08,737 --> 00:11:10,207
And when its back is turned,

266
00:11:10,206 --> 00:11:13,106
you can steal
anything you want from it.

267
00:11:13,112 --> 00:11:15,252
Oh, that egg just hit
a cop's horse.

268
00:11:15,250 --> 00:11:17,150
Floor it, Jimmy!
Floor it!

269
00:11:17,153 --> 00:11:19,363
(revving)

270
00:11:20,661 --> 00:11:22,901
(moaning)

271
00:11:26,506 --> 00:11:28,206
Great.
I have to drive 50 miles

272
00:11:28,209 --> 00:11:30,949
to spend my entire weekend
freezing my ass off.

273
00:11:30,948 --> 00:11:34,348
Stone-cold sober,
sitting in seats with no backs,

274
00:11:34,354 --> 00:11:38,304
making awkward conversation
with dads who share way too much

275
00:11:38,296 --> 00:11:39,796
about their marriages...

276
00:11:39,799 --> 00:11:42,509
I told Sarah when we got
married, "I am a foot guy."

277
00:11:42,505 --> 00:11:44,705
Please guess the one part
of the body

278
00:11:44,709 --> 00:11:46,809
