295
00:12:38,750 --> 00:12:40,750
Uh, socks?

296
00:12:40,754 --> 00:12:42,224
No socks?

297
00:12:47,467 --> 00:12:49,467
All right, all right,
tomorrow is the finals.

298
00:12:49,471 --> 00:12:51,911
(whoops)
Hockey's gonna be over!

299
00:12:51,910 --> 00:12:54,350
- If we win,
it's on to the regionals.
- D'oh!

300
00:12:54,348 --> 00:12:55,648
- Then states.
- D'oh!

301
00:12:55,651 --> 00:12:57,091
- Tri-states.
- D'oh!

302
00:12:57,087 --> 00:12:59,357
Quad-states, nationals,
and then tri-nationals.

303
00:12:59,358 --> 00:13:01,198
(moaning)

304
00:13:01,195 --> 00:13:03,465
But first, we take on
King Toots' team.

305
00:13:03,466 --> 00:13:06,936
The same puck-nuts what
humiliated us the last time.

306
00:13:06,940 --> 00:13:08,810
But I know we're gonna
win this game,

307
00:13:08,810 --> 00:13:12,050
because we got
our little hotshot MVP.

308
00:13:12,050 --> 00:13:14,890
That's right,
our Most Violent Puncher.

309
00:13:14,889 --> 00:13:16,559
- Nelson Muntz.
- (gasps)
- Huh?

310
00:13:17,628 --> 00:13:18,628
(Bart grumbles)

311
00:13:18,630 --> 00:13:20,930
(cheering)

312
00:13:20,934 --> 00:13:23,514
I score every goal
on this team.

313
00:13:26,111 --> 00:13:29,051
- (phone chimes)
- And who the hell is texting me?

314
00:13:29,051 --> 00:13:32,161
"Estee Dionne Malip?"

315
00:13:32,157 --> 00:13:34,827
Uh, does anybody know
what this, uh,

316
00:13:34,829 --> 00:13:36,969
"Estee Dionne Malip" is about?

317
00:13:36,966 --> 00:13:39,666
Hey, I'm dealing with
an Estee Dionne Malip?

318
00:13:39,672 --> 00:13:42,882
Anybody? I don't even know
who the hell I got this from.

319
00:13:42,878 --> 00:13:45,448
(groans) I'm just gonna
send it to my junk.

320
00:13:45,450 --> 00:13:47,320
(laughing)

321
00:13:47,320 --> 00:13:49,790
What? What is-what is funny
about that?

322
00:13:49,792 --> 00:13:52,002
- (laughing)
- (grunts)

323
00:13:51,996 --> 00:13:53,896
Show some respect to Coach.

324
00:13:53,900 --> 00:13:56,440
Why? His car is a converted
washing machine

325
00:13:56,438 --> 00:13:58,208
and his wallet is a rat trap.

326
00:13:59,712 --> 00:14:01,822
- (snaps)
- (groaning) Aah!

327
00:14:01,816 --> 00:14:03,746
(laughing)

328
00:14:03,754 --> 00:14:05,624
Simpson's dead.

329
00:14:05,624 --> 00:14:09,904
<i>Bart Simpson is your primary.
Bart Simpson is your primary.</i>

330
00:14:09,899 --> 00:14:12,639
(chuckling):
Oh, he is such a scuzz.

331
00:14:12,638 --> 00:14:14,138
So am I.

332
00:14:14,141 --> 00:14:16,881
You're not my primary.
He is.

333
00:14:16,880 --> 00:14:19,790
- (grunts)
- Ow!

334
00:14:19,786 --> 00:14:20,786
(gasping)

335
00:14:20,788 --> 00:14:23,428
(panting)

336
00:14:23,426 --> 00:14:25,126
- (groaning)
- Doc, is he gonna be all right?

337
00:14:25,129 --> 00:14:29,839
Yes. But I'm afraid his travel
hockey season is over.

338
00:14:33,613 --> 00:14:35,623
(muffled grunt)

339
00:14:35,617 --> 00:14:37,417
(Homer whoops)

340
00:14:38,389 --> 00:14:39,989
(moaning)

341
00:14:41,295 --> 00:14:44,735
What... what have you done?
Bart was our only chance to win.

342
00:14:44,736 --> 00:14:47,306
You were supposed
to protect your primary!

343
00:14:47,307 --> 00:14:49,107
I... I was.

344
00:14:49,111 --> 00:14:51,451
Like hell you was.
Why'd I ever believe in you?

345
00:14:51,448 --> 00:14:53,948
Y-You're just a fist.
Nothing more.

346
00:14:53,954 --> 00:14:55,524
Get off of my team!

347
00:14:55,524 --> 00:14:56,834
(gulps)

348
00:14:56,826 --> 00:14:59,396
Don't look at me.
I'm not crying!

349
00:15:00,399 --> 00:15:02,199
(sobbing)

350
00:15:03,339 --> 00:15:04,639
(grunts)

351
00:15:09,017 --> 00:15:13,057
I just feel like "hockey team"
is still a smidge too big.

352
00:15:13,058 --> 00:15:15,328
Do you have any smaller letters?

353
00:15:16,198 --> 00:15:19,468
I'm no goon.
I'm just a fist.

354
00:15:21,743 --> 00:15:24,383
And this last stop in hell

355
00:15:24,381 --> 00:15:26,151
is where I belong.

356
00:15:26,953 --> 00:15:28,563
(inhales, exhales)

357
00:15:31,261 --> 00:15:33,531
♪

358
00:15:34,869 --> 00:15:36,369
Afternoon there, ma'am.

359
00:15:36,371 --> 00:15:37,811
Uh, I'm Moe Szysl...

360
00:15:37,808 --> 00:15:39,208
Yeah, can you hurry it up?

361
00:15:39,211 --> 00:15:42,381
I got to eat this when
it's fresh off the zapper.

362
00:15:42,383 --> 00:15:43,493
It's about your kid.

363
00:15:43,486 --> 00:15:45,856
I was his hockey coach
and I yelled some stuff

364
00:15:45,858 --> 00:15:47,958
that might have kicked
his heart in the plums.

365
00:15:47,962 --> 00:15:50,072
Oh, so you're
Coach Sizzle-slacks,

366
00:15:50,066 --> 00:15:52,366
the guy he calls his primary.

367
00:15:52,370 --> 00:15:55,140
What? Nelson thinks
I'm his primary?

368
00:15:55,143 --> 00:15:57,383
- You sure about this?
- Yup.

369
00:15:57,380 --> 00:16:00,720
He yelled the whole story
at the window dog.

370
00:16:00,721 --> 00:16:02,391
(growling)

371
00:16:02,390 --> 00:16:04,830
Nelson wasn't being a psycho
towards Bart.

372
00:16:04,829 --> 00:16:07,169
He was being a goon for me.

373
00:16:07,167 --> 00:16:08,497
Do you know where he went?

374
00:16:08,503 --> 00:16:10,973
He said something about
walking the streets.

375
00:16:10,974 --> 00:16:13,584
Coming to a fateful decision
or whatnot.

376
00:16:13,580 --> 00:16:15,120
Eh. Kid stuff.

377
00:16:15,116 --> 00:16:17,486
I got to find him
before he does something crazy.

378
00:16:19,659 --> 00:16:20,959
Nelson Muntz.

379
00:16:20,961 --> 00:16:23,371
Your reputation precedes you.

380
00:16:23,365 --> 00:16:26,065
I hear you're a dingus
to be respected.

381
00:16:26,071 --> 00:16:28,111
I'm just a fist with no code.

382
00:16:28,108 --> 00:16:30,878
Figure I'll be working
for you sooner or later,

383
00:16:30,881 --> 00:16:33,451
so why not get it over with?

384
00:16:36,291 --> 00:16:39,501
I have a gift for smelling out
good henchmen.

385
00:16:39,497 --> 00:16:40,567
(sniffing)

386
00:16:40,567 --> 00:16:43,267
I'm getting hints
of barely-suppressed rage

387
00:16:43,272 --> 00:16:45,482
with top notes
of "nothing matters" and...

388
00:16:45,476 --> 00:16:46,746
(sniffing)

389
00:16:46,746 --> 00:16:50,286
...a deep finish of abandonment
by a male role model.

390
00:16:50,286 --> 00:16:53,026
Smell all you want.
It won't fix anything.

391
00:16:53,025 --> 00:16:54,225
Just tell me who to hurt.

392
00:16:54,227 --> 00:16:56,327
Want me to get him a lead pipe?

393
00:16:56,331 --> 00:17:00,541
Let's start him out easy. PVC.

394
00:17:06,084 --> 00:17:08,564
How you doing, son?
Can you move?

395
00:17:08,557 --> 00:17:10,527
A little, but it hurts.

396
00:17:10,527 --> 00:17:11,957
I meant can you
move off the couch.

397
00:17:11,963 --> 00:17:15,543
I'm about to enjoy my first
hockey-free weekend in months.

398
00:17:15,537 --> 00:17:17,637
Ooh, hockey!

399
00:17:17,641 --> 00:17:19,781
(grunting)

400
00:17:20,714 --> 00:17:23,854
Homer, get up.
You and Bart are gonna be late.

401
00:17:23,853 --> 00:17:26,193
What? He's useless.
Doc said so.

402
00:17:26,191 --> 00:17:29,031
He can't play any sport
that I have to drive him to.

403
00:17:29,030 --> 00:17:31,940
He has physical therapy,
and the only place

404
00:17:31,936 --> 00:17:35,306
that takes our insurance
is three hours away.

405
00:17:35,309 --> 00:17:38,279
If they ask, Bart is a veteran.

406
00:17:38,282 --> 00:17:39,652
Oh...

407
00:17:42,423 --> 00:17:44,733
Mr. Mayor, I believe
you know the founder

408
00:17:44,729 --> 00:17:48,799
of this vaguely-purposed
yet tax-exempt charity,

409
00:17:48,803 --> 00:17:50,713
my <i>goomar.</i>

410
00:17:50,707 --> 00:17:54,077
Mistresses are the lifeblood
of our community.

411
00:17:58,255 --> 00:18:00,625
Private event.
No pictures.

412
00:18:01,428 --> 00:18:04,328
Well done, Nelly No-Sleeves.

413
00:18:05,938 --> 00:18:07,608
If you'll excuse me,

414
00:18:07,608 --> 00:18:10,748
